# Testing conventions — backend

- **Vitest only.** Never add Jest, `ts-jest`, or Jest-only globals.
- Unit tests live next to services (`*.service.spec.ts`). Mock
  `PrismaService` (and outbound `fetch`) with `vi.fn()` — do not hit a
  real DB in unit tests.
- Use `unplugin-swc` so Nest decorator metadata works under Vitest.
- E2E tests live in `test/**/*.e2e-spec.ts`, use `supertest`, and target
  the separate `parceliq_test` database. Run with
  `yarn workspace backend test:e2e`.
- One behavior per `it(...)`. Prefer asserting HTTP status + wire shape
  over implementation details.
- Root `yarn test` must continue to include `backend/vitest.config.ts`
  via Vitest projects — do not break that wiring.
